Second floor apartment located in the best kept secret of West Seattle in North Admiral just above Alki Beach. Apartment backs a great wall covered in ivy for increased quiet, privacy and natural beauty. Apartment features new carpet, new paint, and a new refrigerator. Apartment includes offstreet parking.

This neighborhood offers the best of both worlds in the north part of West Seattle - a quick urban and forested hike down to Alki Beach and a short walk to all the amenities North Admiral has to offer. Nearby amenities include a movie theater, restaurants, Safeway, PCC, Met Market, Alki Mail and Dispatch, bars, and dry cleaning. You'll have access to the many and varied public spaces, including Hiawatha Park, Schmitz Park, and the College Street Ravine. Several gorgeous sunset overlooks are a quick walk away. Elementary, middle and high schools are all located roughly a mile away.

Public transportation options are many. Within one block you have access to Metro routes 50, 55, 56, and 775. Route 50 takes you to the Alaskan Junction, Delridge, Sodo and Beacon Hill. Routes 56 and 57 will get you to downtown during weekday commute times in as little as 30 minutes. The 775 shuttle takes you to the West Seattle foot ferry which goes to downtown.

Rent includes a separate storage unit (roughly 100 sq ft) and your own personal non-coin-op washer and dryer. Bring or acquire a chest freezer as the storage unit is stubbed for power!

QUESTIONS + More about the Building:
WSG: $50 flat rate per month for WSG bill (water, sewer, and garbage - same rate for 11 years, while Seattle fees are up over 65% in 11 years.
What to bring: driver's license, past landlord phone number(s), 2 checks ($40 ap fee, and $800 Holding Deposit only if you love the place, refundable if not approved, applied to 1st month's rent if approved.)
PETS: this is a nice clean apartment, with a "no pets" policy ... however I know it's possible to have a cat and keep the unit immaculate, so you are welcome to negotiate as part of your application.
Washer: we respectfully avoid in Each Unit, since sadly installing washer in a closet = a mold factory.
LAUNDRY: We provide a "cleaned weekly" Laundry Room, with shelving for Soaps, as well as Storage Lockers.
SMOKING: No smoking Building / Courtyard / Sidewalks (not within 25 feet of the property please).
RECYCLING: all of our buildings provide Food Compost, Yard Waste, Recycle, and Trash bins.
STORAGE: Large, Heated "floor to ceiling" storage facilities.
PARKING: Free Parking on street, or an optional $80 reserved stall.
MOLD: this Building is completely mold free.
Zero chance of "Air B&B", or similar aggressive uses
(great community, with thoughtful long term Residents.)
NOTE: I manage 19 buildings by the Park, and this one for 20+ years, it is one of our favorites.
ONE AP is good for all 19 ... so you are welcome to note your housing needs on your Application.

This information will be accessed as part of the screening of any applications for tenancy: 
- All information on your Application for Tenancy. 
- Your rental history via any identifiable prior Landlords 
- Credit reports via a third party Consumer Reporting Agency 
- Public records regarding criminal conviction history or registration as a sex offender 
- Personal references. 
- Verification of employment and/or income (or rental subsidy) amounts. 
- Public records regarding civil court records.

They work directly with you and you choose whether to share results with us. - For applicants with prior rental history, To apply for tenancy:

2. Complete the online application and pay the application fee.
3. Send a confirming email to us so we know to look for your application. Include a photograph of your government issued ID. 
4. Watch your email for any requests for additional information. You must respond within 72 hours. 
5. Residents over 18 years of age must submit a separate application, For two occupants, the application will not be considered to be complete until both have submitted their application. 
6. If you are approved for tenancy, you must accept the offer in writing and pay a holding deposit of $1000 by cash, certified check or money order within 24 hours of notification. You must agree to the occupancy and accept all terms, if not accepted, we will proceed to the next applicant. 

favorable references must be received from the last two landlords (i.e., timely rent payment, no damage in excess of normal wear and tear, no documented rules violations, timely issuance of notices of intent to vacate and compliance therewith).

- For applicants without prior rental history, adequate personal references equivalent to two favorable past landlord references. 

Sharing results with us is required to complete application.

Welcome to the Clairemont Apartments! Be the first to tour and experience our fully renovated 1 & 2 bedroom apartments and make them your new home! To apply for tenancy:
1. You must first have a tour of the interior and exterior of the building. Applications are not accepted unless all applicants have viewed the property. For applicants from out of the area, one member of the group of residents or another individual identified by the applicant must visit the property in person and use skype, facetime, or another interactive "real time" method of taking a virtual tour of the property on behalf of those not present in person.
3. An application without proof of identity is not complete.
4. Remember that all residents over 18 years of age must submit a separate application and in the case of a group of occupants, the application will not be considered to be complete until all members of the group have submitted their application.
5. If you are approved for tenancy, you must accept the offer within $48.00(hours) in writing and pay a holding deposit of $200. by cash or certified funds ( check or money order) within 48 hours of the time we notify you. If you wish to accept tenancy, you must agree to the occupancy and rent commencement date set forth in the offer
you receive.

Minimum Screening Criteria:
Employment/ Income History:
o Employment
 Two most recent pay stubs
 Two years steady employment or verification of predictable legal income source.
o Self-employed.
 Previous two years federal form 1040 tax returns, signed and showing predictable income.
 Last three months bank statements.
o Retired, Disabled, Student,etc.
 Verification two years predictable legal income source.
 Income requirement:
o Income to rent ratio 3 to 1. Example; Rent= $2,200 than Income = $6,600.
o Debt to Income Ration not to exceed 35% of applicants income.
 Credit history:
o Fico score minimum 725. and/or,
o Credit history with;
 No recent Charge off's.
 No current over due payments.
 No current Collections.
 No current Judgments.
 Maximum three late payments past twelve months
 No Evictions or Unlawful Detainers.
 Rental History:
o Provide positive reference from housing provider for previous 24 months .
 Left property in good condition without owing for rent, damage, fees.
 No pattern of late rent payments.
 No pattern of complaints.
 Sex Offender Registry Information:
o We perform an individualized assessment of any adult on a county, state, or national sex offender registry to determine whether a business reason exists to deny tenancy. We consider the nature and severity of the offense, the number and type of convictions, the time that has elapsed since the conviction, your age at the time of conviction, evidence of good tenant history before and after conviction, any additional information showing rehabilitation, good conduct, or other factors that you would like us to consider.

Additional Notes:
Landlord does not accept comprehensive reusable consumer screening reports.
The landlord is prohibited from requiring disclosure, asking about, rejecting an
applicant, or taking an adverse action based on any arrest record, conviction record, or criminal history, except for registry information as described in subsections 14.09.025.A.3, 14.09.025.A.4, and 14.09.025.A.5, and subject to the exclusions and legal requirements in Section 14.09.115.
Exceptions to minimum income requirements are applicable for Section 8/subsidized applicants as provided in SMC 14.08.040(F).
SMC 14.09.025.A.3 requires a legitimate business reason analysis before a landlord or any person takes an adverse action based on registry information of an adult prospective occupant, tenant or household member
SMC 14.09.025.A.
4 prohibits taking an adverse action based on registry information of a juvenile prospective occupant, tenant or household member
SMC 14.09.025.A.5 prohibits adverse actions based on registry information against adults if the conviction occurred when the individual was a juvenile. screening when denial of tenancy is required by federal regulations in federally assisted housing.

Stroll to the west end of the block for spectacular views of the Sound and the Olympics from your shared neighborhood bench.

Live in a Piece of Seattle History! - It is not often these grand homes are available for rent but here is your chance to claim an American Foursquare Classic Craftsman or "Seattle Box" as your next home! With its significant detailing at the porch, roof and windows, ornamental bracketing, soaring ceilings and vintage fixtures you will definitely be surrounded by retained early century architecture . A newly completed transformation has helped bring this four bedroom, two bathroom home into modern day use with all new flooring, paint, fantastic chefs' kitchen with all new stainless appliances (including gas cooking), and new den/mudroom or home office with 3/4 bath and new laundry. Gracious front porch opens to the impressive formal entry and grand bannister all welcoming you to high ceilinged rooms, circular floor plan, clinker brick fireplace (ornamental only), bay window in dining room . All four bedrooms are upstairs with one full bath. Bathrooms have traditional hex tile floors, tiled bath/shower. All the comforts of home are found within this artfully remodeled true Seattle treasure!

Unfinished basement with great storage spaces. Third floor features unfinished attic (easily accessible via stairs) also can be used for storage.

Charming front courtyard, newly landscaped grounds, tall fencing surrounding the yard frame the commanding entrance from sidewalk.

Close to the hip Madrona shops and restaurants, Madrona Playground, Pratt Park, Miller Community Center as well as the bustling Capitol Hill neighborhood. Very close distance to downtown as well as easy access to Hwy 520 and I90.

This is one of approximately 2,200 houses that are still in existence out of more than 5,000 that were built by the end of 1906 in Seattle's Central Area, Eastlake, First Hill, Leschi, Madison Park, Madrona, and North Capitol Hill neighborhood

This energy efficient, well maintained home in Pigeon Hill neighborhood has a great floor plan, and is convenient to everything West Seattle has to offer. There is beautiful wood-like tile flooring in the living room and hallway, custom tile work in the kitchen and bathroom, and high quality berber carpet in all 3 bedrooms. Fenced patio area off the back of house leads to a dog run. The gas furnace keeps the house toasty warm, and gas range and water heater are cost effective. The wood stove fireplace insert with blower will heat the whole house when needed, or wanted. Kitchen has dining area and dishwasher. All the rooms are spacious, light and bright, and home sits well above street level, for maximum privacy. Front loader washer, and dryer are Energy Star rated, and the the toilet is an air-pressure flush type, that uses very little water, all making for lower cost for water bills. There are two storage areas: a nice, roomy shed at the end of the carport, and a very large locking closet built into the house, in the carport. 14 acres of walking trails are a block away, and Alki Beach is a 30 to 40 minute walk. Bus lines are 4 blocks away, and access to the WS bridge is less than 2 minutes by car. This is a great home for active people, in a wonderful neighborhood community. There's a nice view of the Seattle skyline from the living room and front porch.

Tenants can either maintain grass and yard or choose to pay to have a landscaper come in to maintain property. Tenants are responsible for all utilities
